spanGrp.span: ‘For us to get to Buenos Aires
Sa köjöũ rö se dö-glö-mĩũ Buenos_Aires
we have to walk on the road.
jenẽra se jenã shkö ñala wa (_)
We have a long way if we are coming from highland.
Se jena (hm) tã'ĩ ñala tsõ se bötöũ-lo mãjuirda
The elders/where there is a place/there is a creek called Kori,
sigeglö-wa të/ mãĩ kã' kajki/ diglö damãu kie rö Kori
where there is a place called Nãmãl Sök [Birds from the Savannah].
mãĩ kã' kajki e-gla kie rö Nãmãl Sök
We go all the way and get to a river called Ceibo.
Jeska se shkö se damĩũ-lo dia ska ra (_) diglö kate Bikës í kie-gẽ rö Bikës
It is big and we have to cross it.
Je rö tã'ĩ jeska se jenã köjöũ
We go uphill to a place
se damãga mãjuir mãĩ kã'kuli magã ska
je kie-gẽ siglö-wa të rö Köchuli
because there is a small creek near.
porke jeska diglö ya/ (_) diglö yaba damãu
there is a road; it is called Palmital Road.
Jeska ñãla mãu je kie-gẽ-ite (_) ñala mãu-mĩ Palmital
We go on and get to Salitre Road.
Jeska se (m) shkö-gẽ damĩu ska ra ñala mãu-mĩ-nẽ rö Salitre
That is another group, the Bribris,
Je rö otre kã'wak nẽ je-wa rö bribri-wa
Thus we take that road and get to Buenos Aires.
Tonse je kenẽga sa mĩ-gẽu-lo-mĩ kögẽu-lo-mĩ dömĩu-lo Buenos_Aires rö Estee
Were we walk, each chunk is huge
mãĩ sa shkö-gẽ ska ra kada kada (r) parte tã'ĩ ñala (eh)
and each place has its name.
kã' rö kie ta jaulë jaulë
At Palmital Crossing there is a place called Rancho Cabecar.
Mãĩ kruse Palmital ska e-gla kã' kie rö (hm) Rancho Kabekar
We go that way to get to Buenos Aires.
Jeska sa shkö-gẽ rö sa dö-glö-mĩu-lo Buenos_Aires ra
There, where the ancestors used to walk long ago,
Jeska jeska nẽ (hm) sigeglö-wa wã/ sigeglö-wa shkö-glö ñãjiñã'ra (_)
there is no road; instead people have built many houses.
jeska je ka ta ta jinẽra tãĩ pe yuájuáu-mĩ
Thus the road is now wider.
Jenẽwa jira ñala rö tã'ĩ keyege (_)
